job_description:
Responsibilities:
- Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain, and improve platform and infrastructure to serve client-side applications
- Owns a product, manage individual project priorities, deadlines, and deliverables
- Lead, mentor, and develop development resources and provide product-related directions
- Work with the executives to define software requirements and take lead on design, operations, and technical implementation
- Estimate time to accomplish programming tasks and commit to meeting all objectives
- Code review and contribute to design patterns and coding standards while being a mentor to other peers
- Participate in brainstorming sessions and contribute innovative and original ideas to company technology, algorithms, and products
- Generate wireframes, architecture design, and technical documents for projects
- Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders such as Product Manager, Business Development Manager, clients, and partners
- Creates and implement a short and long-term strategy in terms of technological growth, including identifying emerging technologies to continuously enhance current products and services

Minimum Qualifications:
- 5+ years of relevant work experience
- Able to act as a lead developer responsible for the planning, completion, and coordination of work activity for the products involving the team of developers
- Experience with one or more general programming languages (e.g. Golang, Python, Node.js, Javascript, React.js, C/C++, Java)
- Familiarity with a relevant and globally supported framework - both front-end and back-end
- Experience in building applications from scratch and decomposing applications into smaller services or modules
- Experience designing, building, and deploying scalable cloud-based solution architectures (e.g. GCP, AWS, Azure, IBM Cloud)
- Experience in building RESTful API from scratch
- Flexible and able to multitask; can work within an ambiguous, fast-moving environment, while also driving toward clarity and solutions; demonstrated resourcefulness in setting priorities
- Experience with agile software development 


Preferred qualifications:
- 2+ years of relevant experience as a team lead
Good command in English; spoken and written
- Experience with one or more of the following areas: Server Backend Distributed and Parallel Systems, Full Stack Development (frontend and backend), Scalable Enterprise Platforms and Applications, Data processing pipeline infrastructure, Blockchain Technology
- Strong fundamentals (OOP, algorithms and data structure)
- Experience in implementing testing platforms and unit tests
- Ability to design a scalable API and messaging service
Experience with basic scripting and automation tasks
- Working knowledge of using a distributed version control system within a team environment (preferably Git)

Related Technology: JavaScript, React.js, Golang, AWS (e.g. QLDB, S3), GCP, Firebase, Blockchain, Elasticsearch, Docker, SQL, Node.js, Python, Restful API

job_qualification: C#, ASP.Net (MVC and Core), Web API, Restful API, Javascript, CSS (Bootstrap).

job_description:
Secretariat finance

-- Provide and clear staff advances in accordance with policies and procedures.
-- Preparing check and get it authorized
-- Maintain up to date records accounting transactions and receipts into the QuickBooks system
-- Processing the international payment/fund transfer applicationNotify the supervisor/management of any problems, concerns, feedback, or conflict of interest regarding financial matters.
-- Assure the security of finance, payroll, and accounting records.
-- Provide support to the Executive Director on matters relating to the improvement of financial systems and procedures.
-- Working with the team to help with project management and prepare for project's financial reports/audits.
-- Other tasks assigned by the supervisor
 

Reporting

-- Prepare quarterly financial report as per donor requirements, ensuring it is complete, accurate and produced on a time to ensure adequate review, approval and submission to the Project Manager.
-- Work with the project team to ensure that all donor-related information is disseminated to project, finance and logistics staff as well as partners to enable them to abide by donor rules and regulations
-- Prepare and consolidate monthly invoices and expense projections. 
-- Analyze differences between the projections and actual spending and submit adjustments as required.
-- Ensure financial reports are produced in compliance with donor policies and requirements
-- Monitor cash flow, prepare cash flow forecasts (consolidate with partners)
